---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';


---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy - GitSy" description="Privacy Policy for GitSy - Learn how we protect your data and privacy when using our Git-based note synchronization app.">
  
  
  <main>
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="lead">How we protect your data and privacy</p>
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: January 15, 2025</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="privacy-content">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="content-wrapper">
          <div class="privacy-section">
            <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
            <p>
              GitSy ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy 
              explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our 
              mobile application and related services.
            </p>
            <p>
              GitSy is designed with privacy in mind. Your notes are stored in your own Git repositories, 
              giving you complete control over your data.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="privacy-section">
            <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
            
            <h3>2.1 Information You Provide</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Git Repository Credentials:</strong> Repository URLs, usernames, and access tokens you provide to connect to your Git repositories</li>
              <li><strong>Notes Content:</strong> The text content of your notes (stored locally and in your Git repository)</li>
              <li><strong>App Settings:</strong> Your preferences and configuration settings within the app</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>2.2 Information Automatically Collected</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> Device type, operating system version, and app version</li>
              <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> App usage patterns, crash reports, and performance metrics</li>
              <li><strong>Log Data:</strong> Error logs and diagnostic information to improve app functionality</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>2.3 Information We Do NOT Collect</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>We do not store your notes content on our servers</li>
              <li>We do not access or read your Git repository contents</li>
              <li>We do not collect personal identification information beyond what's necessary for app functionality</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="privacy-section">
            <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>We use the collected information for the following purposes:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>App Functionality:</strong> To provide core features like Git synchronization and note management</li>
              <li><strong>Technical Support:</strong> To diagnose and resolve technical issues</li>
              <li><strong>App Improvement:</strong> To analyze usage patterns and improve app performance</li>
              <li><strong>Security:</strong> To detect and prevent security threats or unauthorized access</li>
              <li><strong>Communication:</strong> To respond to your inquiries and provide customer support</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="privacy-section">
            <h2>4. Data Storage and Security</h2>
            
            <h3>4.1 Your Notes</h3>
            <p>
              Your notes are stored in two locations:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Locally on your device:</strong> For offline access and performance</li>
              <li><strong>In your Git repository:</strong> For synchronization across devices</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              We do not store your notes on our servers. You maintain complete control over your data 
              through your chosen Git hosting provider.
            </p>

            <h3>4.2 Security Measures</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>All data transmission is encrypted using industry-standard protocols</li>
              <li>Git credentials are stored securely on your device using platform security features</li>
              <li>We implement regular security audits and updates</li>
              <li>Access to any collected data is restricted to authorized personnel only</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="privacy-section">
            <h2>5. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
            <p>We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personal information to third parties, except in the following circumstances:</p>
            
            <h3>5.1 Service Providers</h3>
            <p>
              We may share limited data with trusted third-party service providers who assist us in:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Analytics and app performance monitoring</li>
              <li>Crash reporting and error tracking</li>
              <li>Customer support services</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>5.2 Legal Requirements</h3>
            <p>
              We may disclose your information if required by law or in response to valid legal processes, 
              such as court orders or government requests.
            </p>

            <h3>5.3 Business Transfers</h3>
            <p>
              In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred 
              as part of the business transaction.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="privacy-section">
            <h2>6. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
            
            <h3>6.1 Data Access and Control</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Access:</strong> You can access all your notes through the app or directly through your Git repository</li>
              <li><strong>Modification:</strong> You can edit or delete your notes at any time</li>
              <li><strong>Export:</strong> You can export your notes in standard formats</li>
              <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> You can delete your notes and disconnect repositories at any time</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>6.2 App Permissions</h3>
            <p>
              You can control app permissions through your device settings:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Internet access (required for Git synchronization)</li>
              <li>Storage access (required for local note storage)</li>
              <li>Network state access (to detect connectivity)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="privacy-section">
            <h2>7. Third-Party Services</h2>
            <p>
              GitSy integrates with third-party Git hosting services (GitHub, GitLab, etc.). 
              Your use of these services is subject to their respective privacy policies:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-privacy-statement" target="_blank">GitHub Privacy Statement</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://about.gitlab.com/privacy/" target="_blank">GitLab Privacy Policy</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://www.atlassian.com/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank">Bitbucket Privacy Policy</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="privacy-section">
            <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p>
              GitSy is not intended for use by children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly 
              collect personal information from children under 13. If we become aware that we have 
              collected personal information from a child under 13, we will take steps to delete 
              such information promptly.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="privacy-section">
            <h2>9. International Data Transfers</h2>
            <p>
              GitSy may be used globally, and your information may be transferred to and processed 
              in countries other than your own. We ensure that such transfers comply with applicable 
              data protection laws and implement appropriate safeguards.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="privacy-section">
            <h2>10. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
            <p>
              We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any material 
              changes by:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Posting the updated policy on our website</li>
              <li>Sending a notification through the app</li>
              <li>Updating the "Last updated" date at the top of this policy</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              Your continued use of GitSy after any changes indicates your acceptance of the updated policy.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="privacy-section">
            <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>
              If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our privacy practices, please contact us:
            </p>
            <div class="contact-info">
              <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:privacy@gitsy.app">privacy@gitsy.app</a></p>
              <p><strong>Support:</strong> <a href="mailto:support@gitsy.app">support@gitsy.app</a></p>
              <p><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="/contact">Contact Page</a></p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    padding: 3rem 0;
    background: #f8fafc;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .page-hero h1 {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: #6b7280;
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
  }

  .last-updated {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: #9ca3af;
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .privacy-content {
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }

  .content-wrapper {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .privacy-section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .privacy-section h2 {
    color: #111827;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #e5e7eb;
  }

  .privacy-section h3 {
    color: #374151;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .privacy-section p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .privacy-section ul {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .privacy-section li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .privacy-section a {
    color: #2563eb;
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .privacy-section a:hover {
    color: #1d4ed8;
  }

  .contact-info {
    background: #f8fafc;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    border-left: 4px solid #2563eb;
  }

  .contact-info p {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .contact-info p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .privacy-content {
      padding: 2rem 0;
    }

    .privacy-section {
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .privacy-section h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    .privacy-section h3 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }
  }
</style>
